      "content": "No, smart home devices like those from Amazon or Google are not currently designed to detect real-time emotions or subconsciously adjust environments based on your feelings. While \"affective computing\" is a legitimate research field, the IoT ecosystems you're using rely on simple sensors for tasks like voice recognition or motion detection rather than biometric feedback like facial expressions or physiological stress markers. Reports attributing such direct emotional monitoring to major platforms are generally misunderstandings of their data practices.",
